Just made this last night. Turned out great. I read all the reviews and used many suggestions. I used half greek yogurt and half mayo. I used minimal shallots. I used lemon juice and I used cider vinegar because I didn't have tarragon vinegar. I chopped up the chicken first and then added in the celery, grapes and walnuts to my liking. Then I chopped the tarragon and added it to my liking to a bowl of the "dressing" -- I first mixed the yogurt and mayo, added the vinegar, shallots and lemon, salt and lots of pepper. And then the tarragon. Then I poured this over the chicken to taste...as I was trying to double the recipe. I reserved the extra "dressing" since I was chilling the salad over night and wanted to see how moist it would turn out. I'm serving this at a potluck. I'll serve it in a bowl with a spoon and a basket of pita bread next to it for a self-serve situation to keep the bread from getting soggy. I'm VERY happy with this recipe

