I poach boneless skinless chicken breasts in a chicken broth, a big bay leaf, and a whole lemon cut thinly on diagonal. I bring the pot to a boil, then, I let it sit covered for about 45 minutes. Remove the chicken adn cube it into the 1/2 inch cubes. DE-lish! And, it adds a wonderful essence to the salad. Also, I toast my walnuts before adding them. Taragon is one of my favorites, but have found that a combination or other favorite herbs work really well too. I have added some finely chopped sun dried tomatoes, some small cubes of fresh mozzerella, and used fresh basil.. yum! I substituted toasted pine nuts for the walnuts and left the recipe the same after that. Love this versatile recipe!!!!

