Rating: 3
I am not normally a fan of chicken salad, but volunteered to make it for a luncheon. After reading other reviews, I made several changes. First, I roasted the chicken. I used a little more toasted walnut, celery, and shallot than called for, for both flavor and texture. Instead of grapes, I dumped in a bag of orange essence Craisins. Used the 1/2 light mayo, 1/2 light sour cream idea. The salad still didn't have enough character, so I added a finely diced apple, some parmisano-reggiano, and more tarragon vinegar. Served with mini croissants, and was quite pleased to have an interesting rendition of chicken salad.

