Rating: 4
I made this for the umpteenth time last night, and it was EXCELLENT! Of course, I have tweaked this recipe to suit our own tastes. I use 3/4 cup low-fat mayo plus 1/3 cup low-fat sour cream, decrease the tarragon and tarragon vinegar slightly, and add a good dash of bottled hot sauce (Maggie) to the dressing mixture. I use three cups of chicken (more than enough), increase the celery to 1-3/4 cups, the red onion to 1/4 cup, the grapes to 2-1/2 cups. This time I added a small, chopped Winesap apple, and it blended in well. If the mixture seems too dry, add a little milk just before serving. GOOD EATING, esp. when it is 100 degees outside!! I serve this with garlic bread, and it is a substantial meal for 4. Since there are only 2 of us, the leftovers tonight will be even better!!! YUM, YUM.

