Rating: 4
I thought this recipe was WONDERFUL!! I poached 5 skinless boneless chicken breasts in chicken broth. Let it cool in the broth and refrigerated it. The following day, I cubed the chicken and put into a bowl. In a food processor, I mixed 1/2 c. mayo, 1/2 shallot, handful of flat leaf parsley, 3 tbsp tarragon vinegar, 1 tsp. dijon mustard, salt and pepper and a squeeze of fresh lemon juice. Mix until creamy. Toss with the cubed chicken. The flavor was incredible!! I loved it. Just when I thought it couldnt get better, adding the walnuts and purple seedless grapes made it DELICIOUS!! I was hesitant to put grapes in the chicken salad, but the flavors complimented each other. My boyfriend said he would eat this everyday!! Definitely a keeper! Thanks for the great recipe!

