Didn't make this but saw it and needed to comment. My mom has made chicken and grapes for the last thirty years. She poaches bone-in chicken with bay leaves, salt and pepper (but I also use leftovers from roast chicken), cuts it in chunks, mixes with scallions, a little mayo (enough to moisten but not drown), fresh parsley, red seedless grapes, a little mustard, some lemon. If you want the BEST version and if you are game for it, add curry powder. Sounds wierd but it is out of this world! Serve in pita with romaine or green leaf lettuce. Awesome at the beach or any potluck. It makes me think this recipe is *too* dressed up, but I am biased. It is NEVER as good as when mama makes it.

